==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indubitable
<hw>In*du"bi*ta*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indubitabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>indubitable</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Dubitable</er>.]</ety> <def>Not dubitable or
doubtful; too evident to admit of doubt; unquestionable; evident;
apparently certain; <as>as, an <ex>indubitable</ex>
conclusion</as>.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>That which is
indubitable.</def></def2></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Unquestionable; evident; incontrovertible;
incontestable; undeniable; irrefragable.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indubitableness</ent>⟦br⟧
